data.name: TSC will manage charging if the car is at any favorite location set in the Tesla navigation system. Note: TSC is unable to detect at which favorite location the car is, so if you charge at a public charger that is configured as favorite in the Tesla navigation system, TSC tries to manage charging based on your solar production at home and might stop charging if you don't have any solar production at home. Moreover, different driver profiles with different favorite addresses might mess this up. It is HIGHLY recommended to only have one favorite location if this setting is enabled.
